    "Model studies have shown that a first-order phase boundary is expected at the finite baryon density, whereas at vanishing B the transition between the QGP and the hadronic matter is a smooth crossover.",
    "In such a scenario, the first-order phase transition line must end at a critical point and in a finite system such as nuclear collisions, the critical point may turn into a critical region (Fig. 33).",
    "More discussions on experimental results and lattice calculations can be found in [4,277].",
    "The energy scan program at RHIC offers unprecedented high-statistics data on nuclear collisions from the centerof-mass energy of √ s NN = 3 GeVfoot_0 to 200 GeV, correspond- ing to the baryonic chemical potential of B = 750 MeV to 20 MeV.",
    "Measured data of net-proton high moments from 200 -39 GeV, i.e., B ∕T ≤ 2, are consistent with the smooth crossover transition [38] as predicted by the firstprincipal LGT calculations (Fig. 33)."
